msgstr ""

#: ../../source/techniques/mongo.rst:128
msgid "When it comes to unit test our application, we usually want to avoid any database connection, making our test suits independent and their execution process quick as possible. But our classes might depend on models that are pulled from the connection instance. What‚Äôs then? The solution is to create fake models. In order to achieve that, we should set up `custom providers </fundamentals/custom-providers>`__ . In fact, each registered model is represented by ``NameModel`` token, where ``Name`` is a model‚Äôs name."
msgstr ""

